        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 23 at 9:26PM MDT until June 23 at 10:15PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>SVREPZ

The National Weather Service in El Paso has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Otero County in south central New Mexico...
East central Dona Ana County in south central New Mexico...

* Until 1015 PM MDT.

* At 926 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles south of
White Sands National Park, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
White Sands National Park, Orogrande, White Sands Missile Range
Main Post, Organ, East Mesa, Dripping Springs, Aguirre Springs,
Portions of Organ Mountains Desert Peaks National Monument, Lake
Lucero, Soledad Canyon, San Augustin Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
